input: Cars drive fast. Trains are quick. Planes fly high.
output:
Cars drive fast. Trains are quick. Planes fly high.

Cars drive fast. Train speed is rapid, but they can't match the speed of cars on highways. Planes, however, reign supreme in their ability to fly high.

Cars, trains, and planes each have unique advantages: cars offer door-to-door convenience, trains provide a comfortable journey, while planes enable long-distance travel at high altitudes.
